[normal]Film Distributors’ Association (
[normal]FDA
[normal])
[normal] is the trade body for UK theatrical film distributors, the 
[normal]companies that release films 
[normal]in cinemas 
[normal]and promote them to audiences, propelling the film value chain into motion
[normal]. The feature films brought to market by FDA
[normal]’s diverse membership
[normal]—
[normal]ranging widely from international blockbusters to classic revivals; and fr
[normal]om British films to productio
[normal]ns of 42 other countries in 2013
[normal]—
[normal]account for 99
[normal]% of UK cinema admissions. Lord 
[normal]Puttnam
[normal] of 
[normal]Queensgate
[normal] 
[normal]CBE
[normal] is FDA’s President. 
[normal]Every theatrical film release is effectively a joint-venture between its distributor and the exhibitors willing to play it, 
[normal]while
[normal] distributors’ launch campaigns typically involve a host of partners, suppliers and media.
[normal]&#xa0;
