[normal].
[normal]              
[normal]Theatrical film distribution is 
[normal]a sophisticated, competitive and dynamic business that depends on 
[normal]product
[normal] and the extent to which it connects with 
[normal]audiences
[normal]. With 1% of the global population, the UK generates 7% of global 
[normal]c
[normal]inema box-office receipts (£1.1
[normal] billion from 172.5 million admiss
[normal]ions in 2012
[normal]). 
[normal]The
[normal] sector operates 
[normal]effectively
[normal] and delivers a significant contribution to the economy in terms of revenue and jobs, as well as the consequent cultural and creative impacts. An economic multiplier effect applies: for every £1 spent on cinem
[normal]a
[normal] tickets, at least a further £3
[normal] is pumped into the economy on directly related expenditure
[normal].
